-- Terna to Invest in Solar Even After Rete Rinnovabile Sale, Repubblica Says
-- B y   L o r e n z o   T o t a r o
-- 2010-10-25T06:23:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-25/terna-to-make-new-investments-in-solar-energy-next-year-repubblica-says.html
Terna SpA, Italy’s national power-
grid operator, will continue investing in solar energy after the
sale of its Rete Rinnovabile Srl unit to U.K. private-equity
firm Terra Firma Capital Partners Ltd., Chief Executive Officer
 Flavio Cattaneo  told la Repubblica in an interview.  Cattaneo said further investments will be announced at the
beginning of 2011 with the company’s new business plan, the
Rome-based newspaper cited Cattaneo as saying.  The sale of solar unit Rete Rinnovabile for as much as 670
million euros ($936 million) will be completed March 31,
according to an Oct. 18 statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Lorenzo Totaro  in Rome at 
 ltotaro@bloomberg.net   To contact the editors responsible for this story:
John Fraher at   jfraher@bloomberg.net  